# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .gitignore conventions for this plugin
#
# Patterns for "specific directories at the repo root" MUST start with `/` to
# anchor them. A bare directory pattern (no leading `/`) matches at any depth
# and can silently exclude plugin assets that share the same directory name.
# Historical incident: an unanchored `consume/` rule (the old name for the
# user-output `reading/` directory) silently matched `skills/consume/` and
# excluded `skills/consume/SKILL.md` from the initial commit. Don't repeat it.
#
# Patterns for "leaf files that can appear anywhere" (e.g. `.DS_Store`,
# `*.pyc`) are intentionally unanchored — they should match at any depth.
#
# After modifying this file, run `tools/check-tracked.sh` to confirm the
# expected set of plugin assets is still tracked.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# User-generated research output (per-user, not part of the plugin)
/research/
/data/
/reading/
/.checkpoint/

# Local Claude Code state (per-user, never distributed)
/.claude/settings.json
/.claude/settings.local.json

# Python bytecode
tools/__pycache__/
*.pyc

# OS junk (anywhere in tree)
.DS_Store
